   - [ ] `dynamic.Interface` - Dynamic client for unstructured resources\n28: - [ ] Implement `GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n29:   - [ ] Fetch runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1 AgentRuntime resource\n30:   - [ ] Return error if not found\n31: - [ ] Implement `GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n32:   - [ ] Fetch runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1 CodeInterpreter resource\n33:   - [ ] Return error if not found\n34: - [ ] Implement `CreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace string, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n35:   - [ ] Create agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 Sandbox resource\n36:   - [ ] Return created resource or error\n37: - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error`\n38:   - [ ] Delete Sandbox resource\n39:   - [ ] Return error if fails\n40: - [ ] Implement `GetPodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxName, namespace string, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured) (string, error)`\n41:   - [ ] Try direct sandboxName lookup\n42:   - [ ] Try Sandbox annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n43:   - [ ] Try label selector for Pod owned by Sandbox\n44:   - [ ] Return Pod IP or error\n45: - [ ] Create `k8s_client_test.go` with unit tests\n46:   - [ ] Test GetAgentRuntime with valid and invalid resources\n47:   - [ ] Test GetCodeInterpreter with valid and invalid resources\n48:   - [ ] Test CreateSandbox creation\n49:   - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox deletion\n50:   - [ ] Test GetPodIP with various strategies\n51: \n52: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/client -run TestK8sClient` to verify K8sClient tests pass\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Task 3: Define API types and internal types\n57: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/api/types.go` - API request/response types\n58: - [ ] Define CreateSandboxRequest struct\n59:   - [ ] `Name string` - Workload