r kinds\n109:   - [ ] `AgentRuntimeKind = \"AgentRuntime\"`\n110:   - [ ] `CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`\n111: \n112: **Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/api` and `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/types` to ensure types compile\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ### Task 4: Implement utility functions\n117: - [ ] Implement `RandString(n int) string` in `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/utils.go`\n118:   - [ ] Use charset \"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789\"\n119:   - [ ] Generate n random characters\n120:   - [ ] Return random string\n121: - [ ] Implement `generateSandboxName(workloadName string) string`\n122:   - [ ] Use format \"{workloadName}-{random8}\"\n123:   - [ ] Call RandString(8) for random suffix\n124:   - [ ] Return sandbox name\n125: - [ ] Implement `convertEntryPoints(entryPoints []api.EntryPoint) []types.SandboxEntryPoint`\n126:   - [ ] Convert API EntryPoint to internal SandboxEntryPoint\n127:   - [ ] Map all fields correctly\n128: - [ ] Implement `convertToAPIEntryPoints(entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint) []api.EntryPoint`\n129:   - [ ] Convert internal SandboxEntryPoint to API EntryPoint\n130:   - [ ] Map all fields correctly\n131: - [ ] Create `utils_test.go` with unit tests\n132:   - [ ] Test RandString generates correct length\n133:   - [ ] Test RandString generates valid characters\n134:   - [ ] Test generateSandboxName format\n135:   - [ ] Test generateSandboxName uniqueness\n136:   - [ ] Test entryPoints conversion both ways\n137: \n138: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller -run TestUtils` to verify utility tests pass\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ### Task 5: Implement SandboxController structure\n143: - [ ] Define SandboxController struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/controller.go`\n144:   - [ ] `k8sClient *client.K8sClient` - Kubernetes client\n145:   - [ ] `store store.Store` - Session store interface\n146:   - [ ] `logger logr.Logger` - Logger instanc