{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857123040,"sessionID":"ses_286ab2b71ffeuhqZhIY2gPBnOZ","part":{"id":"prt_d79553c01001TjIqFJYlZ4UFGg","messageID":"msg_d7955308b001qCFLJymubgGVaw","sessionID":"ses_286ab2b71ffeuhqZhIY2gPBnOZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3fa00f1017a94b9fa41236ab881e5d4b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 Delta-Spec\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Implement the Valkey storage provider for the AgentCube session store interface, providing a concrete implementation of the Store interface defined in AR-012 using the Valkey key-value store.\n5: \n6: ## Base Specs\n7: - AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n8: - deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types\n9: - session-store/design.md: Session store design including Store interface and storage implementations\n10: - session-store/spec.md: Session store specification with detailed requirements\n11: \n12: ## Requirements\n13: \n14: ### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\n15: The system SHALL initialize a Valkey client using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` with configuration from environment variables.\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Basic Valkey client setup\n18: - **GIVEN** valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variables\n19: - **WHEN** the Valkey store is initialized\n20: - **THEN** a Valkey client is created with the configured address and password\n21: - **AND** the client successfully pings the Valkey server\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: Store interface implementation\n24: The system SHALL implement the Store interface using Valkey client for all required methods.\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Ping method implementation\n27: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey connection\n28: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n29: - **THEN** it returns nil after successful PING command\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID implementation\n32: - **GIVEN** a session key exists in Valkey\n33: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` is called\n34: - **THEN** it retrieves and unmarshals the SandboxInfo JSON\n35: - **AND** returns the SandboxInfo struct\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox implementation\n38: - **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo\n39: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n40: - **THEN** it stores the JSON and updates indices (expiry and last activity) atomically\n41: - **AND** uses NX (set if not exists) flag to prevent overwrites\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox implementation\n44: - **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo that already exists\n45: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n46: - **THEN** it updates the JSON in Valkey\n47: - **AND** uses XX (set if exists) flag to ensure the session exists\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID implementation\n50: - **GIVEN** a session key exists in Valkey\n51: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` is called\n52: - **THEN** it deletes the session key and removes from both indices\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n55: - **GIVEN** multiple sessions with different expiry times\n56: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n57: - **THEN** it returns sessions with expiry before the specified time\n58: - **AND** respects the limit parameter\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n61: - **GIVEN** multiple sessions with different last activity times\n62: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n63: - **THEN** it returns sessions with last activity before the specified time\n64: - **AND** respects the limit parameter\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity implementation\n67: - **GIVEN** a valid session ID and activity timestamp\n68: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, at)` is called\n69: - **THEN** it updates the last activity index for the session\n70: \n71: ### Requirement: Environment variable configuration\n72: The system SHALL read and validate Valkey connection parameters from environment variables.\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Missing required environment variables\n75: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n76: - **WHEN** Valkey store initialization is attempted\n77: - **THEN** it returns an error indicating the missing required variable\n78: \n79: ### Requirement: Optional Valkey configuration\n80: The system SHALL support optional Valkey-specific configuration through environment variables.\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Cache configuration\n83: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to \"true\"\n84: - **WHEN** Valkey store is initialized\n85: - **THEN** the client is created with cache disabled\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Single client configuration\n88: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to \"true\"\n89: - **WHEN** Valkey store is initialized\n90: - **THEN** the client is created with single client mode\n91: \n92: ### Requirement: Error handling\n93: The system SHALL properly handle Valkey errors and convert them to appropriate package-level errors.\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Valkey connection error\n96: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is unreachable\n97: - **WHEN** any store operation is called\n98: - **THEN** it returns a connection error\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Key not found\n101: - **GIVEN** a session key does not exist in Valkey\n102: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` is called\n103: - **THEN** it returns `ErrNotFound`\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Non-existent session update\n106: - **GIVEN** a session ID that does not exist\n107: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n108: - **THEN** it returns `ErrNotFound`\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Non-existent session activity update\n111: - **GIVEN** a session ID that does not exist\n112: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n113: - **THEN** it returns `ErrNotFound`\n114: \n115: ### Requirement: Validation\n116: The system SHALL validate input parameters before performing store operations.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox nil validation\n119: - **GIVEN** nil SandboxInfo\n120: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n121: - **THEN** it returns an error indicating sandbox cannot be nil\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox empty SessionID validation\n124: - **GIVEN** SandboxInfo with empty SessionID\n125: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n126: - **THEN** it returns an error indicating session ID cannot be empty\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox zero ExpiresAt validation\n129: - **GIVEN** SandboxInfo with zero ExpiresAt\n130: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n131: - **THEN** it returns an error indicating expires at cannot be zero\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox nil validation\n134: - **GIVEN** nil SandboxInfo\n135: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n136: - **THEN** it returns an error indicating sandbox cannot be nil\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox empty SessionID validation\n139: - **GIVEN** SandboxInfo with empty SessionID\n140: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n141: - **THEN** it returns an error indicating session ID cannot be empty\n142: \n143: ### Requirement: Connection lifecycle\n144: The system SHALL properly manage Valkey connection lifecycle including initialization and cleanup.\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Close method\n147: - **GIVEN** an active Valkey connection\n148: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n149: - **THEN** the Valkey client connection is closed\n150: \n151: ### Requirement: Data structures\n152: The system SHALL use appropriate data structures for efficient session management.\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Session storage\n155: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo to store\n156: - **WHEN** stored in Valkey\n157: - **THEN** the session data is stored with key prefix \"session:\"\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Expiry index\n160: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with expiry time\n161: - **WHEN** stored in Valkey\n162: - **THEN** the session ID is added to a sorted set with expiry time as score\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Last activity index\n165: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with last activity time\n166: - **WHEN** stored in Valkey\n167: - **THEN** the session ID is added to a sorted set with last activity time as score\n168: \n169: ### Requirement: Bulk operations\n170: The system SHALL support efficient bulk retrieval operations.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Multiple session retrieval\n173: - **GIVEN** multiple session IDs\n174: - **WHEN** retrieving sandbox data for all sessions\n175: - **THEN** it uses MGET for efficient bulk retrieval\n176: - **AND** returns an array of SandboxInfo structs\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 Delta-Spec\n\n## Purpose\nImplement the Valkey storage provider for the AgentCube session store interface, providing a concrete implementation of the Store interface defined in AR-012 using the Valkey key-value store.\n\n## Base Specs\n- AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n- deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types\n- session-store/design.md: Session store design including Store interface and storage implementations\n- session-store/spec.md: Session store specification with detailed requirements\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\nThe system SHALL initialize a Valkey client using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` with configuration from environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Basic Valkey client setup\n- **GIVEN** valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variables\n- **WHEN** the Valkey store is initialized\n- **THEN** a Valkey client is created with the configured address and password","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857123020,"end":1775857123037}}}}
