{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857182968,"sessionID":"ses_286ab2b71ffeuhqZhIY2gPBnOZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7956289f0014UIRaqBWjzwZfP","messageID":"msg_d795556e0001k2hzCfE7VueKra","sessionID":"ses_286ab2b71ffeuhqZhIY2gPBnOZ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-bedeeba5329b4275843ba018b2fbb261","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/store`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: S\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify Valkey store implementation follows design specifications\n- [ ] Verify `store_valkey.go` implements all Store interface methods\n  - [ ] Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n  - [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - [ ] StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n  - [ ] UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n  - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n  - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - [ ] UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n  - [ ] Close() error\n- [ ] Verify valkeyStore struct has required fields\n  - [ ] cli valkey.Client\n  - [ ] sessionPrefix string\n  - [ ] expiryIndexKey string\n  - [ ] lastActivityIndexKey string\n- [ ] Verify fixed key patterns match design\n  - [ ] sessionPrefix = \"session:\"\n  - [ ] expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"\n  - [ ] lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/store` to ensure the implementation compiles and implements the Store interface\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Verify Valkey client initialization with proper configuration\n- [ ] Verify newValkeyStore function reads VALKEY_ADDR environment variable\n- [ ] Verify InitAddress accepts comma-separated addresses (strings.Split)\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD is read correctly\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false allows empty password\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE uses strconv.ParseBool (strict \"true\" check)\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE uses strconv.ParseBool (strict \"true\" check)\n- [ ] Verify default addr is \"localhost:6379\" when VALKEY_ADDR not set\n- [ ] Verify connection timeout is 5 seconds\n- [ ] Verify KeepAlive is 30 seconds\n- [ ] Verify Ping succeeds on initialization\n\n**Verification**: Review newValkeyStore implementation and test with various environment variable combinations\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Verify Ping method implementation\n- [ ] Verify Ping uses B().Ping() builder pattern\n- [ ] Verify result is converted to string using ToString()\n- [ ] Verify \"PONG\" response check\n- [ ] Verify error is returned if result != \"PONG\"\n- [ ] Verify nil is returned on success\n\n**Verification**: Test Ping method with healthy Valkey connection\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Verify GetSandboxBySessionID implementation\n- [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n- [ ] Verify B().Get().Key(key) builder pattern is used\n- [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used to detect empty responses\n- [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned for nil responses\n- [ ] Verify AsBytes() is used to extract data\n- [ ] Verify unmarshalSandboxInfo is called to deserialize JSON\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping with context\n\n**Verification**: Test GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existent sessions\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Verify StoreSandbox implementation with validation\n- [ ] Verify nil sandboxStore validation returns error\n- [ ] Verify empty SessionID validation returns error\n- [ ] Verify zero ExpiresAt validation returns error\n- [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n- [ ] Verify marshalSandboxInfo is called to serialize JSON\n- [ ] Verify B().Set().Key().Value().Nx() builder pattern for SETNX\n- [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for expiry index with ExpiresAt.Unix()\n- [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for last activity index with time.Now().Unix()\n- [ ] Verify all three commands are executed (currently using sequential loop, may need DoMulti)\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping for all operations\n\n**Verification**: Test StoreSandbox with valid data, nil data, empty sessionID, and zero ExpiresAt\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Verify UpdateSandbox implementation with validation\n- [ ] Verify nil sandboxStore validation returns error\n- [ ] Verify empty SessionID validation returns error\n- [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n- [ ] Verify marshalSandboxInfo is called to serialize JSON\n- [ ] Verify B().Set().Key().Value().Xx() builder pattern for SETXX\n- [ ] Verify result is checked using ToString() == \"OK\"\n- [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned if result != \"OK\"\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n\n**Verification**: Test UpdateSandbox with existing and non-existent sessions, nil data, and empty sessionID\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Verify DeleteSandboxBySessionID implementation\n- [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n- [ ] Verify B().Del().Key() builder pattern for main key deletion\n- [ ] Verify B().Zrem().Key().Member() for expiry index removal\n- [ ] Verify B().Zrem().Key().Member() for last activity index removal\n- [ ] Verify all three commands are executed (currently using sequential loop, may need DoMulti)\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n\n**Verification**: Test DeleteSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existent sessions\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Verify ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n- [ ] Verify B().Zrangebyscore() builder pattern is used\n- [ ] Verify Min(\"-inf\") is set for lower bound\n- [ ] Verify Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())) is set for upper bound\n- [ ] Verify Limit(0, limit) is set correctly\n- [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n- [ ] Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs is called with session IDs\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n\n**Verification**: Test ListExpiredSandboxes with multiple sessions and different expiry times\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Verify ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n- [ ] Verify B().Zrangebyscore() builder pattern is used on lastActivityIndexKey\n- [ ] Verify Min(\"-inf\") is set for lower bound\n- [ ] Verify Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())) is set for upper bound\n- [ ] Verify Limit(0, limit) is set correctly\n- [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n- [ ] Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs is called with session IDs\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n\n**Verification**: Test ListInactiveSandboxes with multiple sessions and different activity times\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Verify UpdateSessionLastActivity implementation\n- [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n- [ ] Verify B().Exists().Key() builder pattern is used\n- [ ] Verify ToInt64() is used to check existence\n- [ ] Verify exists == 1 check (session must exist)\n- [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned if exists != 1\n- [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for updating last activity\n- [ ] Verify score uses at.Unix()\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n\n**Verification**: Test UpdateSessionLastActivity with existing and non-existent sessions\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Verify Close method implementation\n- [ ] Verify cli.Close() is called\n- [ ] Verify nil is returned after closing\n\n**Verification**: Test Close method and verify connection is properly closed\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs helper implementation\n- [ ] Verify empty sessionIDs returns empty slice\n- [ ] Verify keys are constructed with sessionPrefix\n- [ ] Verify B().Mget().Key(keys...) builder pattern is used\n- [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n- [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used to skip nil values\n- [ ] Verify AsBytes() is used to extract data\n- [ ] Verify unmarshalSandboxInfo is called for each value\n- [ ] Verify klog.Warningf is used for errors but processing continues\n- [ ] Verify result slice is built correctly\n\n**Verification**: Test getSandboxesBySessionIDs with multiple session IDs and missing keys\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Verify singleton pattern supports Valkey\n- [ ] Verify valkeyStoreType constant is \"valkey\"\n- [ ] Verify initStore() handles valkeyStoreType case\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_ADDR environment variable is read\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD environment variable is read\n- [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false is handled\n- [ ] Verify newValkeyStore is called with correct parameters\n- [ ] Verify storeInstance is set correctly\n\n**Verification**: Test singleton initialization with STORE_TYPE=valkey\n\n---\n\n### Task 14: Add unit tests for Valkey store (if missing)\n- [ ] Create test for Ping method\n  - [ ] Test successful ping\n  - [ ] Test connection failure\n- [ ] Create test for GetSandboxBySessionID\n  - [ ] Test with existing session\n  - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n  - [ ] Test with invalid session ID\n- [ ] Create test for StoreSandbox\n  - [ ] Test with valid data\n  - [ ] Test with nil data\n  - [ ] Test with empty sessionID\n  - [ ] Test with zero ExpiresAt\n- [ ] Create test for UpdateSandbox\n  - [ ] Test with existing session\n  - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n  - [ ] Test with nil data\n  - [ ] Test with empty sessionID\n- [ ] Create test for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n  - [ ] Test with existing session\n  - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n- [ ] Create test for ListExpiredSandboxes\n  - [ ] Test with multiple expired sessions\n  - [ ] Test with no expired sessions\n  - [ ] Test with limit\n- [ ] Create test for ListInactiveSandboxes\n  - [ ] Test with multiple inactive sessions\n  - [ ] Test with no inactive sessions\n  - [ ] Test with limit\n- [ ] Create test for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n  - [ ] Test with existing session\n  - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n- [ ] Create test for Close method\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/store -run TestValkeyStore` to verify all tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 15: Add integration tests for Valkey store\n- [ ] Create TestValkeyStoreE2E test\n  - [ ] Test complete sandbox lifecycle\n  - [ ] Test Store -> Get -> Update -> Delete flow\n  - [ ] Verify indices are updated correctly\n  - [ ] Verify error handling\n- [ ] Create TestValkeyStoreConcurrent test\n  - [ ] Test concurrent Store operations\n  - [ ] Test concurrent Get operations\n  - [ ] Test concurrent Update operations\n  - [ ] Test concurrent Delete operations\n- [ ] Create TestValkeyStoreIndexConsistency test\n  - [ ] Verify expiry index consistency\n  - [ ] Verify last activity index consistency\n  - [ ] Verify index cleanup on deletion\n\n**Verification**: Run integration tests with real Valkey instance\n\n---\n\n### Task 16: Verify error handling consistency with Redis implementation\n- [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned for non-existent keys\n- [ ] Verify error messages are consistent with Redis implementation\n- [ ] Verify validation errors match Redis implementation patterns\n- [ ] Verify all errors are properly wrapped with context\n\n**Verification**: Compare error handling between store_valkey.go and store_redis.go\n\n---\n\n### Task 17: Verify ZSET score semantics match design\n- [ ] Verify expiry index score uses ExpiresAt.Unix() (not time.Now())\n- [ ] Verify last activity index uses time.Now().Unix() on StoreSandbox\n- [ ] Verify last activity index uses at.Unix() on UpdateSessionLastActivity\n- [ ] Verify scores are float64 as required\n\n**Verification**: Review StoreSandbox and UpdateSessionLastActivity implementations\n\n---\n\n### Task 18: Verify MGET batch loading implementation\n- [ ] Verify MGET is used in getSandboxesBySessionIDs\n- [ ] Verify comment about slot requirement is present (for cluster deployments)\n- [ ] Verify error handling for batch operations\n- [ ] Verify nil value skipping is correct\n\n**Verification**: Review getSandboxesBySessionIDs implementation and add comment if missing\n\n---\n\n### Task 19: Verify Valkey-specific behaviors\n- [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used for nil detection (not redis.Nil)\n- [ ] Verify ToString() == \"OK\" check for operation success\n- [ ] Verify builder pattern B() is used for all commands\n- [ ] Verify DoMulti or sequential loop for atomic operations (document choice)\n\n**Verification**: Review all Valkey API calls and verify correct usage\n\n---\n\n### Task 20: Run full test suite and verify code quality\n- [ ] Run all tests: `go test ./pkg/store -v`\n  - [ ] Verify Valkey tests pass\n  - [ ] Verify Redis tests still pass (regression check)\n  - [ ] Verify singleton tests pass\n- [ ] Run static analysis: `go vet ./pkg/store`\n  - [ ] Fix any warnings or errors\n- [ ] Run linter if configured\n  - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n- [ ] Run gofmt: `gofmt -s -w ./pkg/store`\n  - [ ] Ensure code is properly formatted\n- [ ] Update go.mod: `go mod tidy`\n  - [ ] Verify valkey-go dependency is present\n- [ ] Build package: `go build ./pkg/store`\n  - [ ] Verify all packages build successfully\n\n**Verification**: All tests pass, code is linted, packages build successfully\n\n---\n\n### Task 21: Update documentation\n- [ ] Update pkg/store/README.md (if exists) with Valkey information\n  - [ ] Document STORE_TYPE=valkey configuration\n  - [ ] Document VALKEY_ADDR, VALKEY_PASSWORD environment variables\n  - [ ] Document optional VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE and VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n  - [ ] Document Valkey cluster considerations (MGET slot requirement)\n  - [ ] Add usage examples\n- [ ] Add inline code comments if needed\n  - [ ] Document Valkey-specific behaviors\n  - [ ] Document design choices (e.g., sequential vs DoMulti)\n- [ ] Update CHANGE.md status to Completed\n- [ ] Update delta-spec with implementation notes if needed\n\n**Verification**: Review documentation for completeness and accuracy\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Total Tasks**: 21\n**Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 4-6 hours\n\n### Key Deliverables\n1. **Valkey Store Implementation** - Complete Store interface implementation using valkey-go\n2. **Configuration Support** - Environment variable configuration for Valkey connection\n3. **Unit Tests** - Comprehensive unit tests for all methods\n4. **Integration Tests** - End-to-end tests with real Valkey instance\n5. **Singleton Integration** - Valkey support in singleton pattern\n6. **Documentation** - Updated documentation and usage examples\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n- Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n- All Store interface methods implemented correctly\n- Error handling consistent with Redis implementation\n- Configuration follows design specifications\n- Code passes static analysis and linting\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n\n### Dependencies\n- Go 1.24+\n- Valkey server (for testing)\n- github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.x\n- AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n\n### Blocked By\n- None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n\n### Blocks\n- None (this is a foundational component for AR-014)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go\">\nERROR [50:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go\">\nERROR [57:3] unknown field MetricsBindAddress in struct literal of type controllerruntime.Options\nERROR [58:3] unknown field Port in struct literal of type controllerruntim