{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857186048,"sessionID":"ses_286ab2b71ffeuhqZhIY2gPBnOZ","part":{"id":"prt_d795634dc001KiKdTRgvDSAx8v","messageID":"msg_d795629320013Tp1ZlcNGL5LVv","sessionID":"ses_286ab2b71ffeuhqZhIY2gPBnOZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bb100e332cd24d5dac93555f592dfdbd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `pkg/store`\n4: **Language**: Go\n5: **Size**: S\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Verify Valkey store implementation follows design specifications\n11: - [ ] Verify `store_valkey.go` implements all Store interface methods\n12:   - [ ] Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n13:   - [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n14:   - [ ] StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n15:   - [ ] UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n16:   - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n17:   - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n18:   - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n19:   - [ ] UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n20:   - [ ] Close() error\n21: - [ ] Verify valkeyStore struct has required fields\n22:   - [ ] cli valkey.Client\n23:   - [ ] sessionPrefix string\n24:   - [ ] expiryIndexKey string\n25:   - [ ] lastActivityIndexKey string\n26: - [ ] Verify fixed key patterns match design\n27:   - [ ] sessionPrefix = \"session:\"\n28:   - [ ] expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"\n29:   - [ ] lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n30: \n31: **Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/store` to ensure the implementation compiles and implements the Store interface\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Task 2: Verify Valkey client initialization with proper configuration\n36: - [ ] Verify newValkeyStore function reads VALKEY_ADDR environment variable\n37: - [ ] Verify InitAddress accepts comma-separated addresses (strings.Split)\n38: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD is read correctly\n39: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false allows empty password\n40: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE uses strconv.ParseBool (strict \"true\" check)\n41: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE uses strconv.ParseBool (strict \"true\" check)\n42: - [ ] Verify default addr is \"localhost:6379\" when VALKEY_ADDR not set\n43: - [ ] Verify connection timeout is 5 seconds\n44: - [ ] Verify KeepAlive is 30 seconds\n45: - [ ] Verify Ping succeeds on initialization\n46: \n47: **Verification**: Review newValkeyStore implementation and test with various environment variable combinations\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Task 3: Verify Ping method implementation\n52: - [ ] Verify Ping uses B().Ping() builder pattern\n53: - [ ] Verify result is converted to string using ToString()\n54: - [ ] Verify \"PONG\" response check\n55: - [ ] Verify error is returned if result != \"PONG\"\n56: - [ ] Verify nil is returned on success\n57: \n58: **Verification**: Test Ping method with healthy Valkey connection\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Task 4: Verify GetSandboxBySessionID implementation\n63: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n64: - [ ] Verify B().Get().Key(key) builder pattern is used\n65: - [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used to detect empty responses\n66: - [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned for nil responses\n67: - [ ] Verify AsBytes() is used to extract data\n68: - [ ] Verify unmarshalSandboxInfo is called to deserialize JSON\n69: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping with context\n70: \n71: **Verification**: Test GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existent sessions\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### Task 5: Verify StoreSandbox implementation with validation\n76: - [ ] Verify nil sandboxStore validation returns error\n77: - [ ] Verify empty SessionID validation returns error\n78: - [ ] Verify zero ExpiresAt validation returns error\n79: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n80: - [ ] Verify marshalSandboxInfo is called to serialize JSON\n81: - [ ] Verify B().Set().Key().Value().Nx() builder pattern for SETNX\n82: - [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for expiry index with ExpiresAt.Unix()\n83: - [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for last activity index with time.Now().Unix()\n84: - [ ] Verify all three commands are executed (currently using sequential loop, may need DoMulti)\n85: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping for all operations\n86: \n87: **Verification**: Test StoreSandbox with valid data, nil data, empty sessionID, and zero ExpiresAt\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Task 6: Verify UpdateSandbox implementation with validation\n92: - [ ] Verify nil sandboxStore validation returns error\n93: - [ ] Verify empty SessionID validation returns error\n94: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n95: - [ ] Verify marshalSandboxInfo is called to serialize JSON\n96: - [ ] Verify B().Set().Key().Value().Xx() builder pattern for SETXX\n97: - [ ] Verify result is checked using ToString() == \"OK\"\n98: - [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned if result != \"OK\"\n99: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n100: \n101: **Verification**: Test UpdateSandbox with existing and non-existent sessions, nil data, and empty sessionID\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Task 7: Verify DeleteSandboxBySessionID implementation\n106: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n107: - [ ] Verify B().Del().Key() builder pattern for main key deletion\n108: - [ ] Verify B().Zrem().Key().Member() for expiry index removal\n109: - [ ] Verify B().Zrem().Key().Member() for last activity index removal\n110: - [ ] Verify all three commands are executed (currently using sequential loop, may need DoMulti)\n111: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n112: \n113: **Verification**: Test DeleteSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existent sessions\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Task 8: Verify ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n118: - [ ] Verify B().Zrangebyscore() builder pattern is used\n119: - [ ] Verify Min(\"-inf\") is set for lower bound\n120: - [ ] Verify Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())) is set for upper bound\n121: - [ ] Verify Limit(0, limit) is set correctly\n122: - [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n123: - [ ] Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs is called with session IDs\n124: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n125: \n126: **Verification**: Test ListExpiredSandboxes with multiple sessions and different expiry times\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ### Task 9: Verify ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n131: - [ ] Verify B().Zrangebyscore() builder pattern is used on lastActivityIndexKey\n132: - [ ] Verify Min(\"-inf\") is set for lower bound\n133: - [ ] Verify Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())) is set for upper bound\n134: - [ ] Verify Limit(0, limit) is set correctly\n135: - [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n136: - [ ] Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs is called with session IDs\n137: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n138: \n139: **Verification**: Test ListInactiveSandboxes with multiple sessions and different activity times\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### Task 10: Verify UpdateSessionLastActivity implementation\n144: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n145: - [ ] Verify B().Exists().Key() builder pattern is used\n146: - [ ] Verify ToInt64() is used to check existence\n147: - [ ] Verif